nd debate issues such as Jewish nationality and statehood independently of other Communists, and Jewish Communism remained a significant force in Jewish life until the mid-1950s.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunismxHistoryxHistory. 0aCommunismxHistory. 0aJewish communistsxHistory. 4aHistory : History. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Sociology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Communism, Post-Communism & Socialism.2bisacsh1 aCullen, Stephen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEstraikh, Gennady, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffman, Hoffman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffman, Matthew B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffman, Matthew B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHoffman, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendes, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReiter, Ester, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaks, David Yoram, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSrebrnik, Henry F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSrebrnik, Henry F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSrebrnik, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoung, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846220240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438462202423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9